guide: Â§7Carrots and potatoes from killing
Â§7Zombies in graveyard do count.
Â§7Use /warp trapper to accept a quest
Â§7and use SkyHanni's Trapper features
Â§7to make this easier. Bring a bow with you.
Â§7Mine Diamonds in the Mines of Divan
Â§7(HotM 3) or in the carts in the Dwarven Mines.
Â§7You can also passively work on this by using
Â§7Diamond Spreadings in your Minions if you want.
Â§7Wear armor enchanted with Growth 5
Â§7(Enchanting Level 5).
Â§7Applying Growth 5 costs 50 Levels each.
Â§7Kill t2 Revenant Horrors to passively
Â§7progress in the Community Goal.
Â§7Optimal tool:
Â§7Golden Axe with Efficiency 5
Â§7Reforges: Double-Bit or Lush
Â§7Get Haste 3 from a splash to instamine wood
Â§7Forage in The Park to get wood for your minions.
Â§7Place as many minions as you can
Â§7give them a medium storage and the best fuel
Â§7you can. Collect them in time.
Â§7You will gain progress here passively
Â§7while going for other grinds.
Â§7Â§lMake sure to always have a pet active!
Â§7Use a Silk Touch and Efficiency Golden Axe and
Â§7chop mushroom blocks in the Mushroom Desert.
Â§7Optimal tool:
Â§7Golden Axe with Efficiency 5
Â§7Reforges: Double-Bit or Lush
Â§7Get Haste 3 from a splash to instamine wood
Â§7Costs 256 Enchanted Oak Wood to craft and
Â§7unlocks at Oak Wood Collection 9 (30k).
Â§7Get Enchanting Level 10 and play
Â§7the highest experiments in the
Â§7Experimentation Table that you can get.
Â§7Kill endermen and mine Nodes for
Â§7Enchanted Ender Pearls. You need them for
Â§7Enchanted Eyes of Ender (32 of those).
Â§7Don't forget to buy your daily Blaze Powder
Â§7from the Alchemist in the Hub.

21.description: Â§7Equip an Uncommon or higher tiered Rock Pet
guide: Â§7You get the Rock Pet from mining ores.
Â§7The Common Rock unlocks at 2.5k broken ores,
Â§7the Uncommon one at 7.5k. You can also upgrade
Â§7your common rock at Kat but this will take a day.
Â§7Farm in the Garden. Remember Crop Milestones
Â§7grant a lot of XP. Carrots can also benefit this
Â§7as you can use pet candies made out of them to
Â§7contribute to another goal.
Â§7Fish in The Park and make sure rain is active.
Â§7Do not stand/have your bobber under solid blocks
Â§7as this will slow your speed down by a lot.
Â§7You will get this passively by leveling up
Â§7skills, if you don't forget to put the money
Â§7in your bank ;-)
Â§7Craft some easy minions while also getting
Â§7those that will help with this Bingo.
Â§7You might wanna go further than that to
Â§7help with other goals.
Â§7Craft Leather, Iron, Gold and Diamond Armor
Â§7Collect Ender Armor from The End (8 pieces including equipment)
Â§7Craft Leaflet, Farm Suit, Mushroom and Cactus Armor
Â§7Buy Squire, Rosetta's, Celeste and Starlight Armor from Rosetta
Â§7You will unlock this while going
Â§7for Mushroom Collector.
Â§7Remember to get the Glowstone Dust
Â§7by buying a Glowstone from The Builder
Â§7and breaking it on your island.
Â§7Going for the Slayer Goal will give you
Â§7quite some progress here if you do it
Â§7on your own with Revenant Bosses.
Â§7Reforge your Void Sword to Sharp
Â§7at the Blacksmith in the Hub (-28 69 -125),
Â§7or enchant any weapon with Critical 5 (costs 50 Levels).
Â§7You might also get it from receiving a Splash.
Â§7Kill Cows in The Barn to unlock this
Â§7and craft it using the materials you
Â§7got along the way.
Â§7Follow the Lone Adventurers quest in The End
Â§7until you get the Bow.
Â§7Apply it to an armor piece using the Blacksmith.
Â§7This can take quite some time and money
Â§7as it is RNG based.
Â§7To help with this, try to make bigger crafts
Â§7by hand for Carpentry levels. Don't forget
Â§7to do some Alchemy with Materials gathered from the Garden.
Â§7Also do your daily experiments and make sure
Â§7to have a pet active at all times
Â§7(any pet works, even level 100).
Â§7Do your daily commissions in the Dwarven Mines
Â§7(and Crystal Hollows). Also participate in any
Â§7active event there that you come across.
